user_at_name: The Lady Dannatt, Lord-Lieutenant of Norfolk
sample_content:
My sincere congratulations to all the #Norfolk recipients in the King's Birthday Honours: each one making a real difference in their communities, workplace, education, research, medicine, charities or youth groups. Norfolk is so proud of you all! https://t.co/xt5GTmiBRC
It is a huge privilege to be HM Lord_Lieutenant of the wonderful County of #Norfolk.   I wish everyone a very happy #NorfolkDay and thank everyone who gives so much to make it a very special place to live. https://t.co/dVY4KSi5tx
A Deputy Lieutenant visited West Raynham  for the First Year Celebration of the Norfolk Constabulary Ceremonial Association. Many of the officers attending provide Royalty Protection at Sandringham whilst others were involved in the Coronation in London or events in Norfolk. https://t.co/ZMC3IUI9bR
A wonderful story of the transformation of Billingford Church thanks to a brilliant local team supported by others.
We are privileged to be in Normandy today for the  80th Commemoration of D-Day, remembering the courage of all those who landed on 6 June and the tragic loss of life of 4,400 troops https://t.co/bzYQLJUpp7
This will be well worth a watch - such amazing story! @gloucesterwreck @NorfolkMuseums
It was a privilege and joy to be with @stmartinsnfk today to welcome HRH The Duke of Gloucester who was able to visit the new St Martin's house  and learn more about this excellent charity
In #Norfolk we are so fortunate to have wonderful, vital and diverse volunteers within our communities, youth and sports organisations, hospitals, schools, the  arts, churches, environmental support, life enhancing charities, elderly care, the judicial system and more @EDP24 https://t.co/TnKypff7tX
A chilly, wet and windy day to add to the challenge of the Norfolk Marathon - but very well done to every competitor.  Knowing you have supported a charity is a prize in itself.
Wishing all Muslims across Norfolk a peaceful and happy Ramadan. https://t.co/85S4jdgbPv
The voluntary sector in #Norfolk is colossal.  My heartfelt thanks to each and everyone of you for all you do for our charities, your communities, our schools, hospitals and so  much more.  Giving of your time is invaluable.  #VolunteersWeek @NorfolkCF
Heartfelt congratulations to Georgina Holloway who has been honoured for her work with first aid charity St John Ambulance with a promotion to Commander of the Order of St John https://t.co/rGhGwvdR0D
What an achievement from @DiabetesNorfolk in supporting 70,000 people in our county.  Great choice of charity to receive support from @norfolkshow
Another wonderful community project - well done all! @NNFoodbank @NorfokCF
Please follow, support and donate if you can, @3dadswalking.  Each lost a beloved daughter to suicide but they have done so much to raise the profile of suicide prevention amongst young people as well as raising over £1million.  The walk concludes in Norfolk 8-11 May.
An excellent and informative visit to @DeltaFireUK to open their new building and witness a demonstration by @Norfolkfire.  Another great example of innovative business in #Norfolk https://t.co/RwGxFyY2fE
The excellent Thetford Business Awards evening was a good opportunity for a Deputy Lieutenant to highlight @TheKingsAwards which are for outstanding achievement by UK businesses https://t.co/PdMAZ2uVRb https://t.co/0K1WOeZMlM
